{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566988","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566988"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:52:12+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:52:12+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18914"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18914","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18914"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.79,0.02,0.05,0.08,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11647"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80178"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11647","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11647"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18914"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65455"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4986"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11349"},{"type":"tags","id":"11358"},{"type":"tags","id":"11360"},{"type":"tags","id":"11361"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11645"},{"type":"tags","id":"11648"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27396"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27397"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44853"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80178","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80178"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 76-year-old woman is admitted to hospital with pneumonia. She has mild cognitive impairment and becomes confused and disoriented during periods of acute illness. During the morning ward round, she is alert and oriented, engaging in discussion about her care. By evening, she appears drowsy and gives inconsistent responses about her treatment preferences.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the appropriate approach to assessing this patient\u0027s decision-making capacity?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Reassess capacity for each decision at relevant times","Wait until discharge to determine capacity","Defer all decisions to the next of kin","Document capacity assessment once per day","Obtain psychiatric consultation for all decisions"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach is to \u003Cstrong\u003Ereassess capacity for each decision at relevant times\u003C/strong\u003E. Decision-making capacity is decision-specific and can fluctuate, particularly in patients with underlying cognitive impairment or acute illness. Regular reassessment ensures appropriate protection of patient autonomy while maintaining safety.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWait until discharge to determine capacity\u003C/strong\u003E - This delays necessary decision-making and fails to protect the patient\u0027s interests during admission\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDefer all decisions to the next of kin\u003C/strong\u003E - This bypasses the patient\u0027s right to make decisions when they have capacity\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDocument capacity assessment once per day\u003C/strong\u003E - This rigid approach fails to account for fluctuations throughout the day and the varying complexity of different decisions\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObtain psychiatric consultation for all decisions\u003C/strong\u003E - While psychiatric input may be valuable in complex cases, requiring it for all decisions is impractical and delays care unnecessarily\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare providers must balance respect for patient autonomy with protection of vulnerable patients. This requires ongoing assessment of capacity, particularly when making significant healthcare decisions.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Decision-making capacity is specific to each decision and can fluctuate over time.","Patients with impaired decision-making capacity require additional safeguards to protect their interests.","Healthcare providers must regularly reassess capacity when working with vulnerable populations."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 18]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Libby C, Wojahn A, Nicolini JR, et al. Competency and Capacity. [Updated 2023 May 29]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK532862/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65455"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18914"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65455","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65455"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-18T07:11:24+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-18T07:12:29+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11647"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80178"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\u2696\ufe0f","name":"Medicolegal","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,